Women running for office face intimidation, harassment and questions about their marital status. They also face opposition from communities steeped in culture.Women hopefuls include Deputy Governor Ruth Odinga, ODM&rsquo;s Rosa Buyu, nominated Senator Joy Gwendo, Kisumu JP chair Atieno Otieno, former Kisumu executive Rose Kisia, Kisumu deputy speaker Pamela Omino, nominated MCA Farida Salim and CCP leader Grace Akumu.Buyu, who lost to Kisumu West MP Olago Aluoch in 2013, said violence makes women shy away from politics.&ldquo;We want parties to nurture women in leadership by ensuring a favourable environment for credible nominations,&rdquo; she said.